      • calculateSuperTypes

        public java.util.List<dedal.CompRole> calculateSuperTypes()
        Calculates the supertypes of the component class after it computes the initial contract that has to be respected by the reconstructed component roles
        Returns:
        A List\ with all the Dedal component roles realized by the current component class (componentClass). The method returns an empty List\ if no component role could have been extracted.

      • calculateSuperTypes

        private java.util.List<dedal.CompRole> calculateSuperTypes(java.lang.Class<?> objectToInspect,
                                                           java.util.Map<java.util.List<dedal.Interface>,java.util.List<dedal.Interface>> initialContract)
        This method recursively extracts component roles.
        Parameters:
        objectToInspect - The object to calculate super-type from
        initialContract - The contract that need to be respected by reconstructed component roles
        Returns:
        A List\ with all the Dedal component roles realized by the current component class (componentClass). The method returns an empty List\ if no component role could have been extracted.

      • computeInitialContract

        private java.util.Map<java.util.List<dedal.Interface>,java.util.List<dedal.Interface>> computeInitialContract()
        This method computes the initial contract for starting the component roles extraction.
        Returns:
        The contract that need to be respected by reconstructed component roles. The returned result is empty if no contract could have been calculated.

      • splitContract

        private java.util.Map<java.util.List<dedal.Interface>,java.util.List<dedal.Interface>> splitContract(java.util.Map<java.util.List<dedal.Interface>,java.util.List<dedal.Interface>> initialContract,

        This method splits a contract into a sub-contract which corresponds to the new contract that is embedded by a component role.
        Parameters:

        superclass - The super class which new contract is addressed to
        Returns:
